metadata.name: The Louvre
metadata.description:
An early morning spent climbing the most famous museum in the world.

With security patrolling the pyramid structure below, I laid as flat as possible as to not be spotted. Not wanting to overstay my “welcome”, I quickly finished taking photos as the sun began to rise and made a run for the streets before even being able to preview the frames I had just captured. By the time my feet hit the ground again, my previous hiding place was illuminated by the sun for the crowds to see.
